ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government which councils are pathfinders for new two-tier models of joint working.

reply.p: Four county areas—Buckinghamshire, Dorset, Hertfordshire and Lincolnshire—are currently enhanced two-tier working pathfinders. This includes the following councils:

tr.td: St. Albans City and District Council

ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government how many hereditaments have a rateable value of (a) between £10,000 and £15,000 in each Government Office Region outside London and (b) between £10,000 and £21,500 in London, according to Valuation Office Agency records.
